03/11/2004
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- A team of NATO experts is in Bulgaria to inspect military airports, the defence ministry announced Tuesday (2 November).
The aim of the visit is to assess operational capacities, infrastructure and modernisation options, in light of Alliance needs.
The ministry says that the air base in Kroumovo and the airports in Bezmer and Kamenets have been upgraded and that the government will seek financing to modernise at least one more military airport.
(Dnevnik, Sega - 03/11/04)
